clump_2d(intervals, num_intervals, num_rows)
     Interval intervals[];
     int num_intervals;
     int num_rows;

Input arguments:

intervals: the input array of intervals
num_intervals: the size of the array, intervals
num_rows: the number of rows in the 2d data set

The function clump_2d returns the number of clumps.  Every time this
function is invoked, make sure to initialize all the clump id's to
NULL_ID, for example,

for (i=0; i<num_intervals; i++)
	intervals[i].id = NULL_ID;





